{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}} '''Francis '''"'''Earl'''"''' Devore''' (December 2, 1889 in [[Macksville, Kansas]] &ndash; November 12, 1928) was an [[United States|American]] [[racecar driver]]. Devore and fellow driver [[Norman Batten]] were aboard the [[SS Vestris|SS ''Vestris'']] when it sank. He is credited with saving the lives of his wife, and Batten's wife. Both Batten and Devore were lost at sea. Reports indicate that Devore was eaten by a shark in the icy waters.
