{{italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Ochyrocera aragogue'' | image = | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | classis = [[Arachnid]]a | ordo = [[spider|Araneae]] | familia = [[Ochyroceratidae]] | genus = ''[[Ochyrocera]]'' | species = '''''O. aragogue''''' | binomial = '''''Ochyrocera aragogue''''' | binomial_authority = Brescovit, Cizauskas & Mota, 2018 | synonyms = }} '''''Ochyrocera aragogue''''' is a species of [[spider]] of the genus ''[[Ochyrocera]]''. It is endemic to [[Brazil]]. It was named after the giant spider Aragog in ''[[Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets]]''.<ref name="Brescovit">{{cite web|last1=Brescovit|first1=Antonio|title=Seven new species of the spider genus Ochyrocera from caves in Floresta Nacional de Carajás, PA, Brazil|url=https://zookeys.pensoft.net/article/19778/list/6/|website=ZooKeys|accessdate=12 January 2018}}</ref>
